stylometry: Optimization is being as efficient as possible.  How can we spend the least time in order to make the most units and maximize our profits. Ex) making tables or chairs.  Constraints - limits on spending, time, etc.  Feasible Region - area that the optimal solution lies.  Corner points - possible optimal solutions.  Input cells - changing cells that can vary based on time, resources, etc.  Output cells - set amounts that change based on the input cells.
